      "notes": [
        "stick] N.E.D. (Stick v.1 15): To hesitate, scruple, be reluctant or unwilling. Const. to (do something). Only with negative. (Now rare.) [Quotes Henry VIII II.ii.124, “They will not stick to say you envied him”.] Face-Royall] Pink (ed. 1935): Here the meaning is simply a “royal face.”"
