    "26": {
      "play": "royal. God may finish it when He will. ’Tis not a hair",
      "notes": [
        "finish it] Deighton (ed. 1893): Make it complete by adding a beard. not a hair amiss] Delius (ed. 1857): Not out of order by so much as a hair because there is no hair on his cheek.—[A quibble on the literal sense of hair and the sense “something small or slight, iota” (N.E.D., Hair sb. 5).]"
