    "29": {
      "play": "he’ll be crowing as if he had writ man ever since his",
      "notes": [
        "he had writ man] N.E.D. (Write v. 11b): To write man, =[to arrive at man's estate; to attain manhood]. [Obs. Quotes this line as its earliest example.]"
