        "bought him in Paul's] For a convenient account of the use of the nave of St. Paul's Cathedral as a market for servants (as well as a meeting place and business exchange), to which the commentators cite many allusions from contemporary literature, see Sh.'s England (1916), ii. 166."
      ]
    },
