    "81": {
      "play": "lattice, and I could discern no part of his face from",
      "notes": [
        "blushing] Tieck (c. 1794; Das Buch, 1920, p. 234): Here apparently means not to be ashamed, but it is the flush that comes from drinking.—[On the progressive form of the verb, see Franz (3 ed., 1924) §634.]",
        "discern] N.E.D. (Discern v. 1): To separate (things, or one thing from another) as distinct; to distinguish and divide. [Obs.]"
      ]
    },
    "82": {
