    "118": {
      "play": "[Enter Ancient Pistol, Bardolph, and Page.]",
      "notes": [
        "Bardolph, and Page.] Q Bardolfs boy may be a misreading of Bardolfe & boy; see p. 493. It is curious that F too should man Bardolph with a boy (whom the editors unanimously consider identical with Falstaff's page), and the reason may be that some one who wrote out the F text, or some earlier transcript on which F is based, likewise read Sh.'s MS. in the same way as the Q compositor, but at the same time realized that Bardolph too was required.—ED."
      ]
    },
