        "afore] Q afore, according to FRANZ (3 ed., 1924, §§424, 558), is a dialectal form.",
        "tirrits] N.E.D. (Tirrit): rare. A fit of fear or temper; an ‘upset’, disturbance of one’s equanimity [quoting only this line and a 19th-century imitation of it]."
      ]
