        "Would] COLLINS (ed. 1927): I.e. should.",
        "nave of a wheel] CLARKE (ed. 1865): A name comprising allusion to Sir John’s combined knavery and rotundity.",
        "have his ears cut off] Miss WINSTANLEY (ed. 1918): A Star-Chamber penalty for defaming royalty."
      ]
