      "play": "MOULDY, coming forward  Here, an it please you.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "113": {
      "play": "SHALLOW: What think you, Sir John? A good-limbed",
      "notes": []
    },
    "114": {
      "play": "fellow, young, strong, and of good friends.",
      "notes": [
        "friends] N.E.D. (Friend sb. 3): A kinsman or near relation. Now only in pl. (one’s) relatives, kinsfolk, ‘people’."
      ]
    },
    "115": {
      "play": "FALSTAFF: Is thy name Mouldy?",
      "notes": []
    },
