      "play": "MOULDY: Yea, an ’t please you.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "117": {
      "play": "FALSTAFF: ’Tis the more time thou wert used.",
      "notes": []
    },
    "118": {
      "play": "SHALLOW: Ha, ha, ha, most excellent, i’ faith! Things",
      "notes": []
    },
    "119": {
      "play": "that are mouldy lack use. Very singular good, in",
      "notes": [
        "singular] N.E.D. (Singular a. 14): Quasi-adv. Singularly. Obs."
      ]
    },
    "120": {
      "play": "faith. Well said, Sir John, very well said.",
      "notes": []
    },
