    "138": {
      "play": "FALSTAFF: Shadow, whose son art thou?",
      "notes": [
        "son] Clarke (ed. 1865): There is a play on the word “son” here, as if it were spelt “sun,” in antithesis to “shadow.”—Staunton (ed. 1858) refers to 1 Henry IV II.iv.395–8.—Wurth (1895, p. 116) quotes John II.i.498–500: “The shadow of myself form’d in her eye; Which, being but the shadow of your son, Becomes a sun and makes your son a shadow”."
      ]
    },
    "139": {
