        "Like enough] N.E.D. (Like adv. 8): Likely, probably. Rare exc. in phr. like enough (colloq. or dial.)."
      ]
    },
    "141": {
      "play": "father’s shadow. So the son of the female is the",
      "notes": []
    },
    "142": {
      "play": "shadow of the male. It is often so, indeed, but much",
      "notes": [
        "much] Q much.—Cambridge Editors (1864, p. 485): We retain the reading of Q, understanding ‘much’ in the ironical sense in which it is often found. See As You Like It IV.iii.2, [“Is it not past two o’clock? And here much Orlando!”] and II.iv.135 [above].—Prowett (4 N. & Q. i, 1868, p. 481) suggests that but much = without much.—Cowl (ed. 1923) quotes Middleton’s"
      ]
    },
    "143": {
