    "144": {
      "play": "SHALLOW: Do you like him, Sir John?",
      "notes": []
    },
    "145": {
      "play": "FALSTAFF: Shadow will serve for summer. Prick him,",
      "notes": [
        "serve for] DEIGHTON (ed. 1893): Do well for; with a pun on serve in its military sense."
      ]
    },
    "146": {
      "play": "for we have a number of shadows to fill up the",
      "notes": [
        "we have] I should think we must have would make better sense.—ED.",
        "shadows] JOHNSON (ed. 1765): That is, we have in the muster-book many names for which we receive pay, though we have not the men.—STEEVENS (ed. 1793) quotes Barnaby Riche's Souldiers Wishe to Britons Welfarre (1604), p. 19: “One speciall meane that a shifting captaine hath to deceivc his prince, is in his number, to take pay for a whole company, when he hath not halfe.”"
      ]
    },
