    "156": {
      "play": "upon his back, and the whole frame stands upon",
      "notes": [
        "his apparel is built upon his back, and the whole frame stands upon pins] COLLINS (ed. 1927): “The whole of his apparel depends upon pins to keep it together.” This is thus a further play on the word prick, “fasten with a pin.”—COWL (ed. 1923): Frame, structure (of rags).—[DEIGHTON (ed. 1893) understands pins to mean Wart's thin legs!]",
        "stands upon] N.E.D. (Stand v. 78c): To rely upon, depend on, trust to. Obs. (78e): To consist of, be composed of; also, to contain as an ingredient. [Obs.]"
      ]
    },
    "157": {
