        "stand my friend] N.E.D. (Stand v. 15c): To stand one's friend, to act the part of a friend to another. Formerly in other similar phrases, as to stand (one's) good lord.—[Cf. IV.iii.86.]"
      ]
    },
    "236": {
      "play": "friend, and here’s four Harry ten-shillings in",
      "notes": []
    },
