      ]
    },
    "38": {
      "play": "WESTMORELAND: Then, my lord,",
      "notes": [
        "Then (my Lord)] This phrase was obviously overlooked by the Q compositor in setting up the type, and when the omission was discovered it was inserted as best might be, on the same line with the next verse, regardless of meter. See pp. 469, 495.—ED."
      ]
    },
    "39": {
      "play": "Unto your Grace do I in chief address",
      "notes": []
    },
