        "] NICHOLSON (3 N. & Q. ix, 1866, p. 529): The Archbishop says—\"I take not on me here as a physician,\" and yet immediately, and in the same breath, adds that he has come to diet and purge rank minds. [He means, Nicholson says, to make a distinction between the physician who diagnoses the fever and the surgeon who lets the patient blood to cure it; he himself plays only the part of the physician, not that of a surgeon. Hence Nicholson's emendation (see textual notes).] take...on me] N.E.D. (Take v. 16a): To assume the part or character of."
