        "seale] I.e. set the seal of (divine) approval on. 100–1. Booke ... Rebellion] A common Shn. metaphor; cf. iii.1.48.—ED.—COWL. (ed. 1923): [Book=] deed [i.e. contract], as in 1 Henry IV iii.1.223 ... The epithet “forged” ... is transferred from “book,” to which it strictly belongs, to “rebellion.”"
