    "119": {
      "play": "of this little kingdom, man, to arm; and then the",
      "notes": [
        "little kingdom, man] Man is also compared to a kingdom explicitly in John iv.ii.246 and Caesar III.i.68, implicitly in Troilus II.iii.170, Macbeth I.iii.140, and Coriolanus I.i.94 ff. The idea is related to that of the microcosm, man as a little world, on which see Miss Anderson (1927), pp. 61 ff."
      ]
